hopobject.body: I came here to study queenstown medical centre doctors In the latter years of his life, LaFontaine’s profile grew; he broke through the fourth wall with a car insurance commercial in 2006, and suddenly a line of work that had been strictly behind the scenes had a face. In that regard, he was exceptional. “I always compare voice-over work to the Gobelins tapestry weavers,” says Kent. “They never came out from behind the tapestry. As a voice-over talent, you’ve got to understand that that is your place.”
